content:
Depends on #26644 (Define the language of sets and state the ZFC axioms)

These two PR's have been there for a month and a half, and there has been some comments that I have not addressed, and I think I would be more motivated to address the comments if a maintainer expresses interest.

This might be a bit of a chicken and egg situation, because a maintainer might not be interested until I address the comments. What should one do in this situation?

And also, is any maintainer interested in this PR?

I'm interested in the sense that anything touching the SetTheory folder is something that I'll involve myself with, but I'm no maintainer, and I also know very little about model theory in particular.
Do we even have proofs in mathlib?
I think we have a lot of proofs yes
not proofs as in inhabitants of a proposition
